cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SI 

This paper discusses a security issue in a decentralized electronic currency system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves modifying the difficulty of each participant, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and network protocols (cs.NI). The paper also presents a quantitative analysis and a high-order Markov chain model, which are related to game theory (cs.GT) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
